The paper deals with computational algebra and the design of efficient algorithms for Grobner basis computations, which is a topic that falls under the scope of computer science. The paper specifically focuses on the sparsity of input polynomials and mixed systems, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of cs.SC (Symbolic Computation), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.SY (Systems and Control), or cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
